div.p:
As touching my life and converſation, though  the conſcience of mine owne infirmities which are open and bare before the All-ſeeing eye, might caſt mee upon the earth, and ſtop my mouth for ſaying ought, But God be mercifull to me a ſinner; 

                  Luke 18. 13. yet ſince by his grace I have beene kept in all my wanderings and temptations, from putting forth my hand to iniquity, or running into any 
                  Pſal. 125. 3. ſcandalous evill, to the wounding of my conſcience, and ſlander of Religion; why ſhould the operation of this grace be buryed in oblivion, and not rather be acknowledged to the eternall praiſe of his power and goodneſſe unto me?
